🔹 FX OPTION (Business Product)
What it is
Gives right (not obligation) to exchange currency at fixed rate
Customer decides whether to use it

Key Points
Premium paid upfront
Maximum loss = premium
Settlement only if exercised
Used for hedging FX risk

Lifecycle
Booked → Active → Waiting → Exercised / Expired → Closed

Money Flow
Booking → Premium posted
Exercise → Currency exchange
Expiry (no exercise) → No settlement
One-Line Rule

FX Option = Choice + Premium + Limited Risk

🔹 ETD (Exchange-Traded Derivative)
What it is
Standardized contract traded on exchange
Mandatory settlement

Key Points
No premium
Margin required
Daily MTM (Mark-to-Market)
Loss can be unlimited

Lifecycle
Trade → Daily MTM → Margin Calls → Settlement → Close

Money Flow
Daily profit/loss settled
Margin adjusted every day
Final settlement is compulsory

One-Line Rule
ETD = Obligation + Daily P&L + Mandatory Settlement

🔹 FXPM (FX Product Management)
What it is
NOT a product
Core processing engine for FX products

Handles
Validation
Lifecycle management
Accounting
Settlement
Reporting & events

Used For
FX Option
ETD
FX Forward
FX Cash

Key Points
Same engine, different product rules
Independent of input (OFS / TIS / UI)
Central focus for automation

One-Line Rule
FXPM = Engine that processes FX trades

